<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<em><strong>No spoilers here, please. <p>
NO SPOILERS HERE!</em></strong> 
</p>
<p>
Sorcerors are to magic what Unbelievers are to melee. They are the all-around best magic users, being able to cast spells from any school using only a single skill. On the downside, they are the worst fighters. They cannot comfortably use any weapon but a Mage Staff, and even with a Mage Staff, they will be unable to achieve anything remotely resembling battle effectiveness. 
</p>
<p>
The energies used for learning <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Documentation_2fMagic#head-68aa61ed7030bb2c9882d88a6df2df0811241cc5"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">Sorcery</a> sap the life force of a Sorcerer, penalising them with the loss of a percentage of their hit points equal to their Sorcery skill score and penalising their combat ability even more strongly. 
</p>
<p>
For more information on magic, schools and spell effects, read more about <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Documentation_2fMagic"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">Magic</a>. 
</p>
<p>
Starting stat modifiers, starting Skills, innate abilities and starting equipment: Please see the in-game help. 
</p>
